3 Egg yolks\
1/4 cup sugar\
1/8 cup cornstarch\
1 tsp flour\
1 cup milk\
1/2 tsp vanilla extract\
1/2 tablespoon butter\
1/4 teaspoon ground cardamom \
\
Whisk together the egg yolks and half of the sugar until the mixture is pale yellow.\'a0Sift in the cornstarch and flour. Mix well.\'a0Place the milk in a saucepan, add the remaining sugar, cardamom, vanilla and bring it just\'a0to a boil. Temper hot mixture over the eggs/sugar whisking constantly. Pour the mixture back into a saucepan\'a0and bring it to a boil stirring constantly. Don't worry if you start to see lumps, it will smooth out\'a0as you stir. Boil for about one or two minutes, mixture\'a0should\'a0be thick. Stir in the butter. Transfer to a bowl and cover the surface\'a0of the pastry cream with plastic wrap placed directly over the top to prevent the formation of the skin. set\'a0aside to cool then refrigerate until cold.}